{"lemma":"أَشُدِّ","slug":"أَشُدِّ","root":"ش.د.د","root_slug":"ش-د-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-د-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَشُدّ","root":"شدد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":8},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21909","n21919","n21920"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B4%D9%8F%D8%AF%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of شَدِيد (šadīd)","examples":[{"text":"at-Tirimmah ibn al-Hakim\nلَنَا ٱلْعَضُدُ ٱلشُّدَّى عَلَى ٱلنَّاسِ وٱلْأُتَى ... عَلَى كُلِّ حَافٍ فِي مَعَدٍّ وَنَاعِلِ","english":"(please add an English translation of this quotation)"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of شَدِيد (šadīd):; stronger, more powerful; strongest, most powerful"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of شَدِيد (šadīd):; more violent, more severe; most violent, most severe"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of شَدِيد (šadīd):; firmer; firmest"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of شَدِيد (šadīd):; harder; hardest"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"completeness; climax; maturity","examples":[{"text":"بَلَغَ أَشُدَّهُ","english":"to attain full maturity; come of legal age; to reach its climax"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Elative of شَدِيد (šadīd)."},"ipa":["/ʔa.ʃadd/","/ʔa.ʃudd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21909","headword_ar":"اشدّ","root":"$d","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, L, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i$odaAdN","text_ar":"اـِشْدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, S, L, K, *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a company of men, A, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had with him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K,) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had with them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a strong beast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong beasts."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L.)       -A2-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^a$ad~a ka*aA","text_ar":"مَا اَشَدَّ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How hard, hard to be borne, vehement, violent, intense,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"how great, is such a thing!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["S","A","L","K"]},{"entry_id":"n21919","headword_ar":"اَشَدُّ","root":"$d","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Possessing the quality of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$id~ap","text_ar":"شِدَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a greater,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the greatest, degree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, hard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. See an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$id~apN","text_ar":"شِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halabota biAls~aAEidi AlA^a$ad~i","text_ar":"حَلَبْتَ بِالسَّاعِدِ الاَشَدِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalabotuhaA Alx","text_ar":"حَلَبْتُهَا الخ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is a prov., expl. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hlb","text_ar":"حلب"},{"kind":"text","text":". And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiYa A^a$ad~uhu","text_ar":"بَقِىَ اَشَدُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The hardest part of it has remained"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is another prov., applied to him who attains a part of that which he wants, and is unable to attain the completion thereof. (TA. [See also Freytag's “ Arab. Prov., ” i. 169.]) [With an indeterminate subst. or inf. n. following it in the accus. case, it supplies the place of a simple epithet denoting the comparative and superlative degrees; as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ad~u sawaAdFA","text_ar":"اَشَدُّ سَوَادًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, black;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ad~u gaDabFA","text_ar":"اَشَدُّ غَضَبًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, angry."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ad~u Aln~ahaAri","text_ar":"اَشَدُّ النَّهَارِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The time when the day is most advanced, the sun being at the highest."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ad~u Aln~ahaAri","text_ar":"شَدُّ النَّهَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n21920","headword_ar":"اَشُدٌّ","root":"$d","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, L, K, &c.,) also pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^u$ud~N","text_ar":"اُشُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Seer, K,) but the latter form is rare, (TA,) is both masc. and fem., (Zj, TA,) and as used in the Kur it has somewhat different meanings: (Az, TA:) in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hat~aY yaboluga A^a$ud~ahu","text_ar":"حَتَّى يَبْلُغَ اَشُدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and other phrases in the Kur, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ud~","text_ar":"اَشُدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is expl. as meaning The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state of strength;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, L, K;) which is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from eighteen to thirty years:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from about seventeen to forty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from thirty to forty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj in another place:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"puberty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, Mgh, L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"firmness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soundness, of judgment, produced by experience:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"puberty together with such maturity as gives evidence of rectitude of conduct"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"course of life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, Az, Mgh, L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which may be at,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before, the age of eighteen years;"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to most of the men of science, and among them Esh-Sháfi'ee; (Zj, Az, L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the extreme term of which is three and thirty years:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"age of forty years;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the Kur xlvi. 14: (L:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ud~N","text_ar":"اَشُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$odudN","text_ar":"اَشْدُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a sing. having a pl. form, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=nukN","text_ar":"ا=نُكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and these two words are [said to be] the only instances of the kind: (S, K: [but see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=nukN","text_ar":"ا=نُكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or a pl. having no proper sing., (S, Mgh, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=saAlN","text_ar":"ا=سَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaAbiylu","text_ar":"اَبَابِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabaAdiydu","text_ar":"عَبَادِيدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*aAkiyru","text_ar":"مَذَاكِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or its sing. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$id~apN","text_ar":"شِدَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AHeyth, S, Mgh, K,) accord. to Sb; and this is good with respect to the meaning, because one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balaga AlgulaAmu $id~atahu","text_ar":"بَلَغَ الغُلَامُ شِدَّتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEolapN","text_ar":"فِعْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"does not form a pl. of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEulN","text_ar":"اَفْعُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) for as to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoEumN","text_ar":"اَنْعُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) which is said by AHeyth to be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niEomapN","text_ar":"نِعْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [and respecting which Mtr says that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ud~N","text_ar":"اَشُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$id~apN","text_ar":"شِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoEumN","text_ar":"اَنْعُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niEomapN","text_ar":"نِعْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", formed by regarding the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"as elided, (Mgh, [and AHeyth says the like,]) it is only pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuEomN","text_ar":"نُعْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu nuEomK","text_ar":"يَوْمُ نُعْمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or its sing. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ad~N","text_ar":"شَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobN","text_ar":"كَلْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akolubN","text_ar":"اَكْلُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$id~N","text_ar":"شِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iy^obN","text_ar":"ذِيْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*ow^ubN","text_ar":"اَذْوُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) accord. to some; (S;) but neither"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ad~N","text_ar":"شَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"nor"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$id~N","text_ar":"شِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has been heard from the Arabs [as sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ud~N","text_ar":"اَشُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and they are only deduced from analogy: (S, K:) or it is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ad~u","text_ar":"اَشَدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not regarded in the formation of this pl. (IJ, from A 'Obeyd.)"}],"source_refs":["Seer","K","TA","Zj","Az","S","L","Mgh","AHeyth"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}